  "text": "Guilt and hedonic consumption [CITATION_1] classify consumption into two categories based on their affective content and motives. Utilitarian consumption is motivated by the desire to satisfy a functional or sensible need, and is often labeled \"practical\" or \"necessary\" in Western culture.",
